===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The result of shortening or [[reduce|reducing]]; [[abridgment]]. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=3}}</ref>
# {{lb|en|linguistics}} A [[shorten]]ed or [[contract]]ed form of a word or phrase, used to [[represent]] the whole, utilizing omission of letters, and sometimes substitution of letters, or duplication of initial letters to signify plurality, including signs such as, +, =, @. {{defdate|Late 16<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# The process of abbreviating. {{defdate|Mid 16<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|music}} A notation used in music score to denote a direction, as pp or mf.
# {{lb|en|music}} One or more dashes through the stem of a note, [[dividing]] it [[respectively]] into [[quavers]], [[semiquavers]], [[demisemiquavers]], or [[hemidemisemiquavers]].
# Any convenient short form used as a substitution for an understood or inferred whole.
#*: the phrase "civil rights" is an ''abbreviation'' for a whole complex of relationships. - '''Pres. Truman's comittee on Civil Rights'''
# {{lb|en|biology}} Loss during [[evolution]] of the final stages of the ancestral [[ontogenetic]] pattern.
# {{lb|en|mathematics}} [[reduction|Reduction]] to lower [[term]]s, as a [[fraction]].

